  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     Bureau R. F. + A. Lands <lb/>6th Division of Sub District Va
     <name type="recipient">Captain R.S. Lacey</name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1867-07-25">July 25, 1867</date>
      <name type="place">Lexington Va </name>
     </dateline>
     <salute/>
    </opener>

    <p>Respectfully returned to Capt. R.S. Lacy Agent 7 Sub Dist Va with the information that I
     visted Bath County and could find no record in the clerks office in regard to the binding of
     Mary Gordon by the Court to S.C. Slavin To settle the matter definitely I obtained the enclosed
     letter from the clerk of the Court who told me he had them in the office this been years +
     could see no note of such a transaction in any of his books. </p>

    <closer>
     <salute/>
     <signed> J.W. Sharp <lb/> Brvt. Maj + A.S.A. Com. <lb/> Rockhedge, Bath + Alleghany Cos. Va
     </signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
